special_kana_explanation: <SpecialKanaExplanation> <explanation> When you have a small や, ゆ, or よ after a かな that ends in い, that い sound is replaced with the や, ゆ, or よ sound. This only applies to かな that end in い e.g き, し, ち ... or it's katakana equivalents. Also be sure to notice that for ち and し, you don't add a y in the romaji. For example, spelling しょ as shyo doesn't work, you just write sho. Same with if it was the other small ゆ, or よ. Shu, sho etc... same with ち. </explanation>  <Examples> <SpecialKanaExplanationExample><AudioUrl>http://d1ymdibvv3e2ww.cloudfront.net/audio/kana/みゃ.mp3</AudioUrl><KanaExample>みゃ</KanaExample><RomajiExample>mya</RomajiExample></SpecialKanaExplanationExample>,<SpecialKanaExplanationExample><AudioUrl>http://d1ymdibvv3e2ww.cloudfront.net/audio/kana/にゅ.mp3</AudioUrl><KanaExample>にゅ</KanaExample><RomajiExample>nyu</RomajiExample></SpecialKanaExplanationExample>,<SpecialKanaExplanationExample><AudioUrl>http://d1ymdibvv3e2ww.cloudfront.net/audio/kana/きょ.mp3</AudioUrl><KanaExample>きょ</KanaExample><RomajiExample>kyo</RomajiExample></SpecialKanaExplanationExample> </Examples> </SpecialKanaExplanation>
